<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880512-0146 </DOCNO><HL> New Zealand's Current Account </HL><SO> </SO><CO> FREST </CO><IN> MON </IN><DATELINE> WELLINGTON, New Zealand  </DATELINE><TEXT>   New Zealand's deficit on its current account narrowed to a seasonally adjusted 100 million New Zealand dollars ($68.8 million) in March from 151 million dollars a year earlier and a revised 105 million dollars in February, the Statistics Department said.    The current account comprises trade in goods and services, as well as some unilateral transfers. In merchandise trade alone, New Zealand posted a March surplus of 168 million dollars, up from 107 million dollars a year earlier and a revised 162 million dollars in February. </TEXT></DOC>